reviews.review_text: Marriage Made In Heaven Yet antoher amazing Matrix from the deft hands of Mr. Seamons.  Outstanding. Great show now with a source that brings out the full power of the night.  This run is certainly deserving of a Road Trips release, but barring that, this source (along with the other Matrix of the next night) will more than suffice.  Thanks once again to Mr. Seamons for some great, great work.
A good one indeed I don't know that I'm quite as enthusiastic as the previous reviewer, but it's a good one nonetheless. It's worth the listen and a download.

Great Sound / Great Althea Just a chill show...chill version of althea!!!!

Have a listen!

Matrix      All I want to listen to are these matrixes, great job!! These are the future. Hoot 
     This Alaska run is smokin, very psychedelic, I really like. Thanks Hunter for your deadication to the music, can't wait for the next show.

Excellent This is a great show overall.  It is full of energy, particularly the first set.  Jack Straw -> Tower -> Mama -> Mexicali is full of life and energy – and is a very interesting segue in and of itself.  Althea comes out of nowhere after Let It Grow and is one of the highlights of the show.  Deal is also hot.

The second set is good, although the band does slow down considerably for Not Fade Away and Black Peter.  Johnny B Goode gets the tempo rolling again, though, and Don't Ease Me In is an unexpected encore piece.

Overall, this is an excellent show – very underrated.  Hunter's tricks did their magic again.  It sounds better than live.
